        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix models.dev pricing cache churn",
        "body": "## Summary\n- accept normal models.dev model/provider churn without freezing the pricing cache\n- reject partial refreshes unless both required pricing sources retain priceable entries\n- preserve removed historical pricing as fallback without overwriting refreshed map keys\n- keep lookup searching when an unpriceable exact-key entry has a priceable historical fallback\n- preserve distinct dated snapshots instead of repricing them through a base-model alias\n\n## Verification\n- `swift test --filter ModelsDevPricingTests` (27 tests passed)\n- `swift test --filter CostUsagePricingTests` (30 tests passed)\n- `swift test --filter CostUsageScannerClaudeFableTests` (7 tests passed)\n- `swift test`\n- `make check` (parser hash current; 0 format/lint violations)\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- structured autoreview clean\n\n## Public model audit\n- synthetic test identifiers are generic\n- retained exact identifiers are documented by their providers\n- audited candidate diff, tests, fixtures, generated metadata, workflows, and log-rendering changes\n\nOfficial references:\n- https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/models/gpt-4o-mini\n- https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/models/gpt-4o\n- https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/about-claude/models/overview\n- https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock/latest/userguide/model-card-anthropic-claude-sonnet-4-6.html\n- https://docs.cloud.google.com/gemini-enterprise-agent-platform/models/partner-models/claude/use-claude\n\nCloses #1438.\n",
